member.summary: Specify if the 'predictive' evaluation graph should be used or not. The predictive graph is more accurate than performance but is also slower. Note that the performance graph will always be evaluated first if it is enabled, so if you have both performance and predictive enabled, you will often be getting results from just the performance graph. In that situation, predictive will only be used if a match cannot be found using the performance graph.
member.param: True to use the performance graph, false to ignore it.
